 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Cross-Sectional Factor Research — S&P 500\n",
    "\n",
    "**Research question:** Which firm characteristics reliably predict cross-sectional stock returns in the S&P 500?\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks through the full factor research process:\n",
    "1. Build 16 factors across momentum, volatility, value, and quality\n",
    "2. Evaluate predictive power via IC analysis (mean IC, ICIR, decay curves)\n",
    "3. Test statistical significance via Fama-MacBeth cross-sectional regressions\n",
    "4. Construct quintile portfolios and verify factor monotonicity\n",
    "5. Walk-forward backtest of a multi-factor composite with turnover control\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "*Universe: S&P 500 constituents (current). Period: 2019–present. Rebalancing: monthly.*\n",
    "\n",
    "**Survivorship bias note:** We use the current S&P 500 list. Dead/delisted stocks are excluded, which slightly overstates returns. A production system would use a point-in-time constituent database (Compustat CRSP)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, \"..\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mticker\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    'figure.facecolor': 'white', 'axes.facecolor': '#f8f9fa',\n",
    "    'axes.grid': True, 'grid.alpha': 0.3, 'font.size': 11,\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "START = '2019-01-01'\n",
    "N_TICKERS = 150  # reduce for faster run; set None for full S&P 500\n",
    "print(f\"Config: START={START}, N_TICKERS={N_TICKERS}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data & Universe"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.data.fetch import (\n",
    "    get_sp500_universe, load_close_panel, load_volume_panel,\n",
    "    load_market_returns, download_fundamentals, compute_returns,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "tickers = get_sp500_universe()[:N_TICKERS] if N_TICKERS else get_sp500_universe()\n",
    "\n",
    "close        = load_close_panel(tickers, start=START)\n",
    "volume       = load_volume_panel(tickers, start=START)\n",
    "mkt_returns  = load_market_returns(start=START)\n",
    "fundamentals = download_fundamentals(tickers)\n",
    "returns_dict = compute_returns(close, periods=[1, 5, 21, 63])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Price panel: {close.shape[0]} days × {close.shape[1]} tickers\")\n",
    "print(f\"Date range: {close.index[0].date()} → {close.index[-1].date()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Fundamentals coverage: {fundamentals.notna().mean().mean():.0%}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1-month return distribution\n",
    "ret_21 = returns_dict[21].stack().dropna()\n",
    "print(f\"\\n1-month returns: mean={ret_21.mean():.2%}, std={ret_21.std():.2%}, skew={ret_21.skew():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Factor Library\n",
    "\n",
    "16 factors across 4 groups, each grounded in peer-reviewed academic literature."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.factors.registry import build_all_factors, factor_summary_table\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"FACTOR LIBRARY:\")\n",
    "display(factor_summary_table())\n",
    "\n",
    "factors = build_all_factors(\n",
    "    close=close, volume=volume,\n",
    "    market_returns=mkt_returns,\n",
    "    fundamentals=fundamentals,\n",
    "    preprocess=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nComputed {len(factors)} factors successfully\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.factors.base import factor_correlation\n",
    "\n",
    "# Factor correlation matrix — critical for understanding redundancy\n",
    "price_factors = {k: v for k, v in factors.items()\n",
    "                 if k in ['MOM_12_1','MOM_6_1','MOM_3_1','STR','IVOL','RVOL','BAB','ILLIQ']}\n",
    "corr = factor_correlation(price_factors)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 7))\n",
    "im = ax.imshow(corr.values, cmap='RdBu_r', vmin=-1, vmax=1)\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(range(len(corr.columns)))\n",
    "ax.set_yticks(range(len(corr.index)))\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(corr.columns, rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
    "ax.set_yticklabels(corr.index)\n",
    "for i in range(len(corr)):\n",
    "    for j in range(len(corr.columns)):\n",
    "        ax.text(j, i, f'{corr.iloc[i,j]:.2f}', ha='center', va='center', fontsize=9)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(im, ax=ax, label='Spearman Correlation')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Factor Cross-Correlation Matrix\\n(Average monthly rank correlation)')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nKey insight: Factors with |corr| < 0.3 are complementary — combining them reduces idiosyncratic noise.\")\n",
    "print(\"Factors with |corr| > 0.7 are redundant — use only one from each high-correlation cluster.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. IC Analysis — Evaluating Predictive Power\n",
    "\n",
    "The IC (Information Coefficient) is the Spearman rank correlation between factor scores and subsequent returns. It is the **primary signal quality metric** at systematic quant funds.\n",
    "\n",
    "- IC > 0.03: weak but potentially useful\n",
    "- IC > 0.05: solid signal  \n",
    "- ICIR > 0.3: good signal quality (\"signal-to-noise ratio\")\n",
    "- t-stat > 2: statistically significant at 5% level"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.analytics.ic_analysis import compute_ic_table, compute_ic_decay_table, ICAnalysis\n",
    "\n",
    "ic_table = compute_ic_table(factors, returns_dict, primary_horizon=21)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"IC SUMMARY TABLE — 21-day horizon\")\n",
    "display(ic_table[['mean_ic','std_ic','icir','t_stat','p_value','pct_positive','n_periods']].round(4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mean IC bar chart\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "ic_sorted = ic_table['mean_ic'].sort_values(ascending=True)\n",
    "colors = ['seagreen' if v > 0 else 'crimson' for v in ic_sorted]\n",
    "ic_sorted.plot.barh(ax=ax, color=colors, alpha=0.85)\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "ax.axvline(0.03, color='green', lw=1.2, ls='--', label='IC = 0.03 (useful threshold)')\n",
    "ax.axvline(-0.03, color='red', lw=1.2, ls='--')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Mean IC by Factor (21-day horizon)')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Mean Spearman IC')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ICIR bar chart\n",
    "ax = axes[1]\n",
    "icir_sorted = ic_table['icir'].sort_values(ascending=True)\n",
    "colors = ['steelblue' if v > 0.3 else ('seagreen' if v > 0 else 'crimson') for v in icir_sorted]\n",
    "icir_sorted.plot.barh(ax=ax, color=colors, alpha=0.85)\n",
    "ax.axvline(0.3, color='green', lw=1.2, ls='--', label='ICIR = 0.3 (good threshold)')\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "ax.set_title('IC Information Ratio (ICIR = Mean IC / Std IC)')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Factor Signal Quality — IC Analysis', fontsize=13)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# IC Decay curves — shows signal half-life\n",
    "ic_decay = compute_ic_decay_table(factors, returns_dict, horizons=[1, 5, 10, 21, 63])\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11, 5))\n",
    "top_factors = ic_table['icir'].abs().nlargest(6).index\n",
    "colors = plt.cm.tab10(np.linspace(0, 0.9, len(top_factors)))\n",
    "\n",
    "for factor, color in zip(top_factors, colors):\n",
    "    if factor in ic_decay.index:\n",
    "        decay = ic_decay.loc[factor]\n",
    "        ax.plot([1,5,10,21,63], decay.values, 'o-', color=color, lw=2, ms=6, label=factor)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.axhline(0, color='black', lw=0.8, ls='--')\n",
    "ax.axhline(0.03, color='green', lw=1, ls=':', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Forecast Horizon (trading days)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Mean IC')\n",
    "ax.set_title('IC Decay Curve — Top 6 Factors\\n(How quickly predictive power fades with horizon)')\n",
    "ax.legend(ncol=2, fontsize=9)\n",
    "ax.set_xscale('log')\n",
    "ax.set_xticks([1, 5, 10, 21, 63])\n",
    "ax.get_xaxis().set_major_formatter(plt.ScalarFormatter())\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Interpretation: Steep decay → signal is short-lived (high turnover needed)\")\n",
    "print(\"Slow decay → signal persists (monthly rebalancing is sufficient)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Cumulative IC for best factor — shows regime changes\n",
    "best_factor = ic_table['icir'].abs().idxmax()\n",
    "ica = ICAnalysis(factors[best_factor], returns_dict, factor_name=best_factor)\n",
    "ica.fit()\n",
    "cum_ic = ica.cumulative_ic(horizon=21)\n",
    "ic_ts  = ica.ic_series(horizon=21)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(13, 6), sharex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].bar(ic_ts.index, ic_ts.values,\n",
    "            color=['seagreen' if v > 0 else 'crimson' for v in ic_ts.values],\n",
    "            alpha=0.7, width=5)\n",
    "axes[0].axhline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "axes[0].axhline(ic_ts.mean(), color='black', lw=1.5, ls='--',\n",
    "                label=f'Mean IC = {ic_ts.mean():.3f}')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title(f'{best_factor} — Monthly IC Time Series')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('IC')\n",
    "axes[0].legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].plot(cum_ic.index, cum_ic.values, color='steelblue', lw=2)\n",
    "axes[1].fill_between(cum_ic.index, cum_ic.values, 0,\n",
    "                     where=cum_ic.values >= 0, alpha=0.15, color='green')\n",
    "axes[1].fill_between(cum_ic.index, cum_ic.values, 0,\n",
    "                     where=cum_ic.values < 0, alpha=0.2, color='red')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Cumulative IC (slope = signal consistency)')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Cumulative IC')\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Fama-MacBeth Regressions\n",
    "\n",
    "Fama-MacBeth tests whether each factor's cross-sectional predictive power is statistically significant **after controlling for common risk exposures**.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Methodology:**\n",
    "1. Each month, regress returns on lagged factor scores (cross-sectionally)\n",
    "2. Collect the monthly slope coefficients λ_t\n",
    "3. Test H₀: E[λ_t] = 0 using **Newey-West t-statistics** (corrects for autocorrelation in λ_t)\n",
    "\n",
    "|t-stat| > 2.0 → significant at 5%. This is the standard test used in academic factor papers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.analytics.fama_macbeth import run_fama_macbeth_panel, FamaMacBeth\n",
    "\n",
    "fm_table = run_fama_macbeth_panel(factors, returns_dict[21], nw_lags=6)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"FAMA-MACBETH RESULTS\")\n",
    "print(\"Newey-West t-statistics (6 lags) | Monthly rebalancing\")\n",
    "display(fm_table[['mean_lambda','t_stat_nw','p_value_nw','significant','annualized','mean_r2']].round(4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# FM t-stats\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "fm_valid = fm_table['t_stat_nw'].dropna().sort_values(ascending=True)\n",
    "colors = ['seagreen' if v > 2 else ('crimson' if v < -2 else 'steelblue') for v in fm_valid]\n",
    "fm_valid.plot.barh(ax=ax, color=colors, alpha=0.85)\n",
    "ax.axvline(2.0, color='green', lw=1.5, ls='--', label='|t|=2.0 (5% significance)')\n",
    "ax.axvline(-2.0, color='green', lw=1.5, ls='--')\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Fama-MacBeth Newey-West t-statistics')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('t-statistic')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Lambda time series for best factor\n",
    "ax = axes[1]\n",
    "best_fm = fm_table['t_stat_nw'].abs().dropna().idxmax()\n",
    "fm_obj = FamaMacBeth(nw_lags=6)\n",
    "ret_m = returns_dict[21].resample('ME').last()\n",
    "f_m = factors[best_fm].resample('ME').last()\n",
    "fm_obj.fit(f_m, ret_m)\n",
    "lam = fm_obj.lambdas['lambda'].dropna()\n",
    "ax.bar(lam.index, lam.values * 100,\n",
    "       color=['seagreen' if v > 0 else 'crimson' for v in lam.values],\n",
    "       alpha=0.75, width=20)\n",
    "ax.axhline(lam.mean() * 100, color='black', lw=1.5, ls='--',\n",
    "           label=f'Mean λ = {lam.mean()*100:.2f}%/month')\n",
    "ax.axhline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "ax.set_title(f'{best_fm} — Monthly λ_t (cross-section slope)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('λ_t (%/month per unit of factor)')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Fama-MacBeth Cross-Sectional Regression Results', fontsize=13)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Quintile Portfolios — Monotonicity Test\n",
    "\n",
    "A robust factor should produce a **monotonic return spread** from Q1 (top-ranked) to Q5 (bottom-ranked). If Q1 > Q2 > Q3 > Q4 > Q5, the factor correctly orders the cross-section.\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Q1-Q5 spread** (long best, short worst) is the pure factor return before portfolio construction."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.portfolio.ranking import MultiFactorRanking, quintile_returns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build rebalancing dates\n",
    "all_dates = returns_dict[21].index\n",
    "monthly = pd.DatetimeIndex(all_dates).to_period('M')\n",
    "rebal_dates = all_dates.groupby(monthly).last()\n",
    "\n",
    "ranker = MultiFactorRanking()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show quintile analysis for top 3 factors by ICIR\n",
    "top3 = ic_table['icir'].abs().nlargest(3).index.tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, len(top3), figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, fname in enumerate(top3):\n",
    "    q_ret = quintile_returns(\n",
    "        {fname: factors[fname]}, returns_dict[21], rebal_dates, ranker\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    q_means = [q_ret[f'Q{q}'].mean() for q in range(1, 6) if f'Q{q}' in q_ret.columns]\n",
    "    ls_mean = q_ret['Q1-Q5'].mean() if 'Q1-Q5' in q_ret.columns else q_means[0] - q_means[-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax = axes[i] if len(top3) > 1 else axes\n",
    "    colors = plt.cm.RdYlGn(np.linspace(0.8, 0.2, len(q_means)))\n",
    "    ax.bar(range(1, len(q_means)+1), [m*100 for m in q_means], color=colors, alpha=0.9)\n",
    "    ax.axhline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'{fname}\\nL/S spread: {ls_mean*100:.2f}%/month')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('Quintile (1=Best)')\n",
    "    if i == 0:\n",
    "        ax.set_ylabel('Avg Monthly Return (%)')\n",
    "    ax.set_xticks(range(1, len(q_means)+1))\n",
    "    ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FormatStrFormatter('%.1f%%'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Quintile Return Monotonicity — Top 3 Factors by ICIR', fontsize=13)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Multi-Factor Walk-Forward Backtest\n",
    "\n",
    "Combining factors reduces reliance on any single signal's regime dependence. The composite uses IC-weighted or equal-weighted factor scores.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Transaction costs:** 5 bps one-way (realistic for S&P 500 large-caps at typical institutional size)  \n",
    "**Turnover control:** max 30% one-way turnover per month prevents excessive costs from rank instability"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.backtest.walk_forward import WalkForwardBacktest\n",
    "\n",
    "composite_factors = {k: factors[k] for k in top3}\n",
    "bt = WalkForwardBacktest(transaction_cost=0.0005, max_turnover=0.30)\n",
    "bt_results = bt.run(composite_factors, returns_dict[21])\n",
    "stats = WalkForwardBacktest.summarize(bt_results)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"WALK-FORWARD BACKTEST RESULTS\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Factors:             {', '.join(top3)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Period:              {bt_results.index[0].date()} → {bt_results.index[-1].date()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Ann. Gross Return:   {stats['ann_gross_ret']:.1%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Ann. Net Return:     {stats['ann_net_ret']:.1%}  (after 5bp one-way TC)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Net Sharpe Ratio:    {stats['net_sharpe']:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Max Drawdown:        {stats['max_drawdown']:.1%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Hit Rate:            {stats['hit_rate']:.1%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Avg Monthly Turnover:{stats['avg_turnover']:.1%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  TC Drag (annual):    {stats['avg_tc_drag_ann']:.2%}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Equity curve\n",
    "ax = axes[0, 0]\n",
    "ax.plot(bt_results.index, bt_results['cumulative_gross'], color='steelblue', lw=1.5, label='Gross')\n",
    "ax.plot(bt_results.index, bt_results['cumulative_net'], color='seagreen', lw=2, label='Net (5bp TC)')\n",
    "ax.axhline(1, color='black', lw=0.8, ls='--')\n",
    "ax.fill_between(bt_results.index, bt_results['cumulative_net'], 1,\n",
    "                where=bt_results['cumulative_net'] >= 1, alpha=0.1, color='green')\n",
    "ax.fill_between(bt_results.index, bt_results['cumulative_net'], 1,\n",
    "                where=bt_results['cumulative_net'] < 1, alpha=0.2, color='red')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Cumulative Return — Multi-Factor L/S')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Growth of $1')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drawdown\n",
    "ax = axes[0, 1]\n",
    "ax.fill_between(bt_results.index, bt_results['drawdown'] * 100, 0, color='crimson', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Drawdown (%)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Drawdown (%)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Monthly returns distribution\n",
    "ax = axes[1, 0]\n",
    "ax.hist(bt_results['net_ret'] * 100, bins=25, color='steelblue', edgecolor='white', alpha=0.8)\n",
    "ax.axvline(bt_results['net_ret'].mean() * 100, color='red', lw=2, ls='--',\n",
    "           label=f\"Mean: {bt_results['net_ret'].mean()*100:.2f}%\")\n",
    "ax.axvline(0, color='black', lw=0.8)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Monthly Return Distribution (Net)')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Monthly Return (%)')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Turnover over time\n",
    "ax = axes[1, 1]\n",
